description.para: The spherical kernel uses basic number types of the algebraic kernel: In fact, the two number types AlgebraicKernelForSpheres::RT and Kernel::RT must refer to the same type, as well as AlgebraicKernelForSpheres::FT and Kernel::FT.
The following types are available, as well as all the functionality on them described in the SphericalKernel concept.
Polynomials_for_circle_3 is implemented as a std::pair< Polynomial_for_spheres_2_3, Polynomial_1_3 > and is a model of AlgebraicKernelForSpheres::PolynomialsForCircles_3.

detaileddescription.para: The first parameter of the spherical kernel must be instantiated with a model of the Kernel concept. The Spherical_kernel_3 class template derives from this first parameter, in order to reuse all needed functionalities on basic objects provided by a model of the Kernel concept.
The second parameter, AlgebraicKernelForSpheres, is meant to provide the spherical kernel with all the algebraic functionalities required for the manipulation of algebraic curves.
